[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":990},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fpython\u002F2021\u002F09\u002F25\u002Fpython-from-js-perspective-24-inheritance\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fpython\u002F2021\u002F09\u002F25\u002Fpython-from-js-perspective-24-inheritance\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fpython\u002F2021\u002F09\u002F25\u002Fpython-from-js-perspective-24-inheritance\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fpython\u002F2021\u002F09\u002F25\u002Fpython-from-js-perspective-24-inheritance\u002F":967,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fpython\u002F2021\u002F09\u002F25\u002Fpython-from-js-perspective-24-inheritance\u002F":976},"\u002Fpython\u002F20210925\u002F2051252749\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":949,"date":950,"description":951,"extension":952,"lang":953,"meta":954,"navigation":108,"path":955,"readingMinutes":956,"seo":957,"standalone":958,"stem":959,"tags":960,"tldr":964,"updated":950,"url":965,"__hash__":966},"content\u002Fen\u002FPython\u002Fpython-from-js-perspective-24-inheritance.md","Learning Python From a JavaScript Angle (24) - Inheritance","1002518245",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":942},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,30,33,323,332,339,513,536,543,547,550,553,575,578,584,591,597,606,637,644,650,699,722,787,790,797,859,865,871,877,883,887,890,893,897,932,938],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"Last time I teased that inheritance was coming up next, so naturally this post is all about inheritance (yeah, obviously).",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"the-idea-of-inheritance","The Idea of Inheritance",[17,25,26],{},"So what is inheritance? Does JavaScript have it? Yep, JavaScript does.",[17,28,29],{},"In short, here's the idea, framed with people. Imagine there's a dad, and he has a son (obviously), and the son inherits some of the dad's biological traits. For example, if the dad's eye color is blue, then the eye color the son inherits is also blue.",[17,31,32],{},"So let me write a quick JavaScript inheritance version first, just as a reference:",[34,35,40],"pre",{"className":36,"code":37,"language":38,"meta":39,"style":39},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","function Father(pupil) {\n  this.pupil = pupil || '藍色'; \u002F\u002F eye color\n}\n\nfunction Son(name) {\n  Father.call(this);\n  this.name = name; \u002F\u002F the son's name\n}\n\nSon.prototype = Object.create(Father.prototype);\nSon.prototype.constructor = Son;\n\nSon.prototype.eyeColor = function() {\n  console.log(this.name + ' 眼睛顏色是：' + this.pupil);\n}\n\nconst ray = new Son('Ray');\nray.eyeColor(); \u002F\u002F Ray 眼睛顏色是：藍色\n","js","",[41,42,43,67,97,103,110,125,142,158,163,168,200,219,224,246,276,281,286,309],"code",{"__ignoreMap":39},[44,45,48,52,56,60,64],"span",{"class":46,"line":47},"line",1,[44,49,51],{"class":50},"sWyjQ","function",[44,53,55],{"class":54},"sj_SG"," Father",[44,57,59],{"class":58},"sMAXC","(",[44,61,63],{"class":62},"s_sBn","pupil",[44,65,66],{"class":58},") {\n",[44,68,70,74,77,80,83,86,90,93],{"class":46,"line":69},2,[44,71,73],{"class":72},"sCcAr","  this",[44,75,76],{"class":58},".pupil ",[44,78,79],{"class":50},"=",[44,81,82],{"class":58}," pupil ",[44,84,85],{"class":50},"||",[44,87,89],{"class":88},"sTRMh"," '藍色'",[44,91,92],{"class":58},"; ",[44,94,96],{"class":95},"sQrFR","\u002F\u002F eye color\n",[44,98,100],{"class":46,"line":99},3,[44,101,102],{"class":58},"}\n",[44,104,106],{"class":46,"line":105},4,[44,107,109],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":108},true,"\n",[44,111,113,115,118,120,123],{"class":46,"line":112},5,[44,114,51],{"class":50},[44,116,117],{"class":54}," Son",[44,119,59],{"class":58},[44,121,122],{"class":62},"name",[44,124,66],{"class":58},[44,126,128,131,134,136,139],{"class":46,"line":127},6,[44,129,130],{"class":58},"  Father.",[44,132,133],{"class":54},"call",[44,135,59],{"class":58},[44,137,138],{"class":72},"this",[44,140,141],{"class":58},");\n",[44,143,145,147,150,152,155],{"class":46,"line":144},7,[44,146,73],{"class":72},[44,148,149],{"class":58},".n