8},[44,500,306],{"class":88},[44,502,141],{"class":58},[44,504,505,507,509,511],{"class":46,"line":311},[44,506,314],{"class":58},[44,508,237],{"class":54},[44,510,319],{"class":58},[44,512,322],{"class":95},[17,514,515,516,518,519,521,522,524,525,529,530,532,533,535],{},"You'll notice the ",[41,517,179],{}," style and the ",[41,520,337],{}," style look pretty different, and the ",[41,523,337],{}," syntax is a lot easier to write. But here's the thing to remember: ",[526,527,528],"strong",{},"JavaScript is still a prototype-oriented language",". ",[41,531,337],{}," is just syntactic sugar — under the hood it's still the ",[41,534,179],{}," concept.",[17,537,538],{},[539,540],"img",{"alt":541,"src":542},"class is great","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FPython\u002F%E5%BE%9E%20JavaScript%20%E8%A7%92%E5%BA%A6%E5%AD%B8%20Python\u002F1631971144677.png",[12,544,546],{"id":545},"inheritance","Inheritance",[17,548,549],{},"Now that we've recapped JavaScript's inheritance concept and syntax, let's pull it back to Python.",[17,551,552],{},"Is Python's inheritance syntax super complicated? Not really. Let's switch to a different practice template — we'll take the JavaScript template from before and build a class out of it:",[34,554,558],{"className":555,"code":556,"language":557,"meta":39,"style":39},"language-py shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","class Father:\n  def __init__(self, pupil):\n    self.pupil = pupil or '藍色'\n","py",[41,559,560,565,570],{"__ignoreMap":39},[44,561,562],{"class":46,"line":47},[44,563,564],{},"class Father:\n",[44,566,567],{"class":46,"line":69},[44,568,569],{},"  def __init__(self, pupil):\n",[44,571,572],{"class":46,"line":99},[44,573,574],{},"    self.pupil = pupil or '藍色'\n",[17,576,577],{},"OK, so how do we write inheritance next?",[17,579,580],{},[539,581],{"alt":582,"src":583},"Definitely uses extends, right?","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FPython\u002F%E5%BE%9E%20JavaScript%20%E8%A7%92%E5%BA%A6%E5%AD%B8%20Python\u002F1630050076486.png",[17,585,586,587,590],{},"Nope, it absolutely does not use the ",[41,588,589],{},"extends"," syntax.",[17,592,593],{},[539,594],{"alt":595,"src":596},"hahahaha","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FPython\u002F%E5%BE%9E%20JavaScript%20%E8%A7%92%E5%BA%A6%E5%AD%B8%20Python\u002F1630050170140.png",[17,598,599,600,602,603,605],{},"Python's inheritance syntax is really clean — you just add parentheses after the ",[41,601,337],{}," name and pass in the name of the ",[41,604,337],{}," you want to inherit from:",[34,607,609],{"className":555,"code":608,"language":557,"meta":39,"style":39},"class Father:\n  def __init__(self, pupil):\n    self.pupil = pupil or '藍色'\n\nclass Son(Father):\n  pass\n",[41,610,611,615,619,623,627,632],{"__ignoreMap":39},[44,612,613],{"class":46,"line":47},[44,614,564],{},[44,616,617],{"class":46,"line":69},[44,618,569],{},[44,620,621],{"class":46,"line":99},[44,622,574],{},[44,624,625],{"class":46,"line":105},[44,626,109],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":108},[44,628,629],{"class":46,"line":112},[44,630,631],{},"class Son(Father):\n",[44,633,634],{"class":46,"line":127},[44,635,636],{},"  pass\n",[17,638,639,640,643],{},"See how simple that is? If you don't know what the ",[41,641,642],{},"pass"," I wrote is for, I'd suggest flipping back to the previous post — I won't explain it again here.",[17,645,646,647,649],{},"Next, let's fill in the rest of ",[41,648,173],{}," and keep going:",[34,651,653],{"className":555,"code":652,"language":557,"meta":39,"style":39},"class Father:\n  def __init__(self, pupil):\n    self.pupil = pupil or '藍色'\n\nclass Son(Father):\n  def __init__(self, name):\n    self.name = name\n\n  def eyeColor(self):\n    print(this.name + ' 眼睛顏色是：' + this.pupil)\n",[41,654,655,659,663,667,671,675,680,685,689,694],{"__ignoreMap":39},[44,656,657],{"class":46,"line":47},[44,658,564],{},[44,660,661],{"class":46,"line":69},[44,662,569],{},[44,664,665],{"class":46,"line":99},[44,666,574],{},[44,668,669],{"class":46,"line":105},[44,670,109],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":108},[44,672,673],{"class":46,"line":112},[44,674,631],{},[44,676,677],{"class":46,"line":127},[44,678,679],{},"  def __init__(self, name):\n",[44,681,682],{"class":46,"line":144},[44,683,684],{},"    self.name = name\n",[44,686,687],{"class":46,"line":160},[44,688,109],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":108},[44,690,691],{"class":46,"line":165},[44,692,693],{},"  def eyeColor(self):\n",[44,695,696],{"class":46,"line":170},[44,697,698],{},"    print(this.name + ' 眼睛顏色是：' + this.pupil)\n",[17,700,701,702,704,705,708,709,712,713,715,716,718,719,721],{},"Now, don't rush to instantiate ",[41,703,173],{}," yet — basically this chunk will throw an error, namely ",[41,706,707],{},"AttributeError: 'Son' object has no attribute 'pupil'",". The main reason is that when we define an ",[41,710,711],{},"__init__"," method in the child class, it overrides the parent class's inherited ",[41,714,711],{},". So here we have to re-inherit ",[41,717,193],{}," again. And there are actually two ways to do that. The first is to use ",[41,720,711],{},":",[34,723,725],{"className":555,"code":724,"language":557,"meta":39,"style":39},"class Father:\n  def __init__(self, pupil):\n    self.pupil = pupil or '藍色'\n\nclass Son(Father):\n  def __init__(self, name):\n    Father.__init__(self, '')\n    self.name = name\n\n  def eyeColor(self):\n    print(self.name + ' 眼睛顏色是：' + self.pupil)\n\nray = Son('Ray')\nray.eyeColor() # Ray 眼睛顏色是：藍色\n",[41,726,727,731,735,739,743,747,751,756,760,764,768,773,777,782],{"__ignoreMap":39},[44,728,729],{"class":46,"line":47},[44,730,564],{},[44,732,733],{"class":46,"line":69},[44,734,569],{},[44,736,737],{"class":46,"line":99},[44,738,574],{},[44,740,741],{"class":46,"line":105},[44,742,109],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":108},[44,744,745],{"class":46,"line":112},[44,746,631],{},[44,748,749],{"class":46,"line":127},[44,750,679],{},[44,752,753],{"class":46,"line":144},[44,754,755],{},"    Father.__init__(self, '')\n",[44,757,758],{"class":46,"line":160},[44,759,684],{},[44,761,762],{"class":46,"line":165},[44,763,109],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":108},[44,765,766],{"class":46,"line":170},[44,767,693],{},[44,769,770],{"class":46,"line":202},[44,771,772],{},"    print(self.name + ' 眼睛顏色是：' + self.pupil)\n",[44,774,775],{"class":46,"line":221},[44,776,109],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":108},[44,778,779],{"class":46,"line":226},[44,780,781],{},"ray = Son('Ray')\n",[44,783,784],{"class":46,"line":248},[44,785,786],{},"ray.eyeColor() # Ray 眼睛顏色是：藍色\n",[17,788,789],{},"With that, the example code above runs just fine.",[17,791,792,793,796],{},"The other way is to use the ",[41,794,795],{},"super"," function to re-inherit:",[34,798,800],{"className":555,"code":799,"language":557,"meta":39,"style":39},"class Father:\n  def __init__(self, pupil):\n    self.pupil = pupil or '藍色'\n\nclass Son(Father):\n  def __init__(self, name):\n    super().__init__('')\n    self.name = name\n\n  def eyeColor(self):\n    print(self.name + ' 眼睛顏色是：' + self.pupil)\n\nray = Son('Ray')\nray.eyeColor() # Ray 眼睛顏色是：藍色\n",[41,801,802,806,810,814,818,822,826,831,835,839,843,847,851,855],{"__ignoreMap":39},[44,803,804],{"class":46,"line":47},[44,805,564],{},[44,807,808],{"class":46,"line":69},[44,809,569],{},[44,811,812],{"class":46,"line":99},[44,813,574],{},[44,815,816],{"class":46,"line":105},[44,817,109],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":108},[44,819,820],{"class":46,"line":112},[44,821,631],{},[44,823,824],{"class":46,"line":127},[44,825,679],{},[44,827,828],{"class":46,"line":144},[44,829,830],{},"    super().__init__('')\n",[44,832,833],{"class":46,"line":160},[44,834,684],{},[44,836,837],{"class":46,"line":165},[44,838,109],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":108},[44,840,841],{"class":46,"line":170},[44,842,693],{},[44,844,845],{"class":46,"line":202},[44,846,772],{},[44,848,849],{"class":46,"line":221},[44,850,109],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":108},[44,852,853],{"class":46,"line":226},[44,854,781],{},[44,856,857],{"class":46,"line":248},[44,858,786],{},[17,860,861,862,864],{},"The nice thing about using ",[41,863,795],{}," is that you don't have to write out the parent class's name. It'll automatically figure out the parent class of whatever class you passed in, and re-inherit the parent's properties and methods for you.",[17,866,867,868,870],{},"So after seeing all this — don't you think Python and JavaScript's ",[41,869,337],{}," have a fair bit in common?",[17,872,873],{},[539,874],{"alt":875,"src":876},"Is this JavaScript?","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FPython\u002F%E5%BE%9E%20JavaScript%20%E8%A7%92%E5%BA%A6%E5%AD%B8%20Python\u002F1624117447047.png",[17,878,879,880,882],{},"And that's pretty much it for this post — it mainly wraps up the leftover ",[41,881,337],{}," material from the previous chapter.",[12,884,886],{"id":885},"a-note-from-the-author","A Note From the Author",[17,888,889],{},"Because of work I'm often pretty busy and don't clean the house much, so I really rely on my little robot vacuum to sweep and mop. But recently, while cleaning out the robot's dust bin...",[17,891,892],{},"I accidentally crushed the dust bin... ugh.",[12,894,896],{"id":895},"about-the-bunnies","About the Bunnies",[898,899,900,909,917,925],"ul",{},[901,902,903],"li",{},[327,904,908],{"href":905,"rel":906},"https:\u002F\u002Ftailwindcss.tw",[907],"nofollow","Tailwind CSS Taiwan official site",[901,910,911,916],{},[327,912,915],{"href":913,"rel":914},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.facebook.com\u002Ftailwindcss.tw",[907],"Tailwind CSS Taiwan"," (Facebook page)",[901,918,919,924],{},[327,920,923],{"href":921,"rel":922},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.facebook.com\u002Fgroups\u002Ftailwindcss.taiwan",[907],"Bunny Sect × Tailwind CSS Taiwan"," (Facebook group)",[901,926,927],{},[327,928,931],{"href":929,"rel":930},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.facebook.com\u002Flalarabbits-%E5%85%94%E5%85%94%E6%95%99%E5%A4%A7%E6%9C%AC%E7%87%9F-102150975410839\u002F",[907],"Bunny Sect